{"questionId":"2581851","questionHtml":"<p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The region enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis is rotated by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo></math> about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis to form a solid sphere. The sphere is drilled through along the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis, creating a cylindrical hole. The resulting spherical ring has height, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>This information is shown in the following diagrams.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong>diagram not to scale</strong></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/7d48d3add591640b5f8fed5221c00d69d11b4ef6.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The spherical ring has a volume of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> cubic units. Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 (subtracting volumes)</strong></p>\n<p>radius of cylinder, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct limits <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>volume of part sphere <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></math></p>\n<p>correct integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integrated expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>recognition that the volume of the ring is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>≠</mo><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>h</mi></math> </em>(or equivalent)<em><br></em></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that the volume of the ring is&nbsp;<em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></math></em> (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integrated expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mroot><mn>6</mn><mn>3</mn></mroot></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (volume of cylindrical hole)</strong></p>\n<p>radius of cylinder, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct limits <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>volume of part sphere <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>correct integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integrated expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>recognition that the volume of the cylindrical hole is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>≠</mo><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>h</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> </em>(or equivalent)<em><br></em></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>24</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> (or equivalent)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mroot><mn>6</mn><mn>3</mn></mroot></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3 (shells)</strong></p>\n<p>radius of cylinder, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use shells method&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mo>∫</mo><mi>x</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>correct limits&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integrated expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mroot><mn>6</mn><mn>3</mn></mroot></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2581851","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.9","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The function f is defined by f(y)=r2-y2 for -r≤y≤r. The region enclosed by the graph of x=f(y) and the y-axis is rotated by 360 ° about the y-axis to form a solid sphere. The spher","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"9","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.17—Areas under curve onto y-axis, volume of revolution (about x and y axes)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectio